    <section class="path-to-cert" id="path-to-certification-1">
        <div class="container-fluid">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-8 col-sm-70">
                    <div class="path-to-cert-content view-more-view-less">
                        <div class="path-to-cert-content-summary">
                            <h2 class="section-heading"> Steps to get PMP certification online </h2>
                            <p style="display:inline;">Strengthen your knowledge and practice of project management processes and concepts with PMI certifications. Validate your expertise as a project management professional with the <b>PMP certification</b> and take advantage of networking opportunities with the best in the industry. Not sure where to start with your PMP certification? Just follow these simple steps.</p><span class="view-more-link">.....</span> <a href="javascript:void(0);" class="view-more-link">View more</a>
                            <div class="view-more-data editor-content" id="path-to-cert-data" style="display:none;">
                                <p><b>1. Get trained&nbsp;</b></p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Confirm your eligibility to become a PMP certified project manager before proceeding.</li>
                                    <li>Register on the PMI website, or become a PMI member and member of your local chapter.</li>
                                    <li>Get enrolled in a PMP Course and undertake 35 hours of PMP Training from an Authorized Training Partner (ATP) like KnowledgeHut to earn 35 PDUs (PMI’s Education requirement).&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
                                </ul>
                                <p><b>2. Take the PMP exam<br></b></p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Check out the PMP classroom training schedules &amp; dates to find a suitable session that meets your requirements.</li>
                                    <li>Sign up for the PMP Exam by filling the PMI application form and submit it to PMI for approval.</li>
                                    <li>PMI will email your eligibility code and payment request once your online application has been confirmed to be complete.</li>
                                    <li>Make a payment for the credential fee ($405 for PMI members; $555 for non-members). </li>
                                    <li>Schedule your PMP exam on the PMI app, my.pmi.org; you can choose to take the exam at a Pearson VUE test center or via the online proctored testing solution.</li>
                                    <li>Develop a detailed study plan and study hard; study the PMBOK Guide thoroughly a few times, as it is one of the primary references for the Exam.</li>
                                    <li>Attend the exam with the necessary documents and aim for a score of at least 80% or higher (this is a guideline rather than a rigid pass percentage criterion as PMI have not published the pass score in recent times).</li>
                                </ul>
                                <p><b>3. Become a certified PMP</b></p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>This is the final step for you to <b>get PMP certified</b>. On passing the exam, you’ll receive a congratulatory email from PMI, typically in about a week or two, after which you will see your name updated in the PMI registry. You have now achieved a <b>Project Management Professional Certification</b>!&nbsp;</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div> <a id="" href="javascript:void(0);" class="view-less-link hide">View Less</a>
