            "name": "Do PMP contact hours expire?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>The PMP contact hours are those&nbsp;that are&nbsp;obtained in a formal learning environment and provided by a standard instructor. </p><p>These are generally&nbsp;35&nbsp;contact&nbsp;hours for project management education&nbsp;and do&nbsp;not expire.&nbsp;Having these contact hours&nbsp;is one of the eligibility requirements&nbsp;to sit for the PMP exam. Once&nbsp;you have it, you can use it to apply for the PMP certification exam. For instance, if you have the education 5 years ago, you can still use it to fulfill the requirement for your PMP certification.</p>"
