            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How do I memorize PMP processes?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>The PMP process chart is an important aspect of the PMBOK® Guide, hence you need to memorize it before you take the exam.</p><p>The six steps below will help you:</p><ol><li>Find a paper and draw a table with 6 columns and 11 rows </li><li>In the 6 columns, write the 5 processes</li><li>In the 11 rows, write the 10 areas of knowledge</li><li>Fill in the processes in each of the corners of the process chart </li><li>Fill the planning column with the processes </li><li>Fill the estimate processes into the planning process group </li><li>Fill the performed processes </li><li>Fill the five develop processes </li><li>Fill the control processes </li><li>Fill the manage processes </li><li>Fill the remaining processes in the PMBOK® Guide</li></ol>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What is the PMP exam prep required to pass the exam?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>The PMP exam is fairly difficult, and it requires adequate preparation.</p><p>Below is what you can do to prepare for the PMP exam:</p><ol><li>Read the PMBOK® Guide </li><li>Read third-party PMP textbooks such as Rita Mulcahy and Andy Crowe’s books. </li><li>Join PMP Exam workshops </li><li>Use online PMP exam simulators </li><li>Join study groups and discussion forums </li><li>Take PMP exam practice questions. </li></ol><p>Make sure you answer at least 85% of the questions correctly. If you get this percentage on your first attempt, then you are well prepared for the exam.</p>"
            }
        }, {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How can I study for the PMP certification exam?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "<p>You can study for the PMP certification exam by reading and understanding the PMBOK® Guide. Decide which learning mode will suit you best. </p><p>How best do you learn? Is it through reading a book, listening to a podcast, watching a video? Understand your learning style and plan your study around it.</p><p>Studying for a certification exam requires partnership. Study in groups and learn from the contribution of others. You need to familiarize yourself with the lexicon of project management as used in the PMBOK® Guide.</p><p>You can also take a <a href=\"https://www.knowledgehut.com/blog/project-management/how-to-prepare-for-pmp-exam\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">PMP prep exam</a> or register for an online practice test and quizzes.</p>"
            }
